JOHANNESBURG - Delegates at the African National Congress (ANC)’s 54th elective conference were in good spirits and fine singing form, despite several hours of delays. Numerous calls by the party's top officials for delegates not to sing factional songs seem to have fallen on deaf ears as delegates inside the plenary hall cleared their lungs to make it clear who they support. Apart from vocalising their preferred candidates, delegates also wanted answers from outgoing ANC president Jacob Zuma.  eNCA